<object id="GUID-CCF19AC8-7CF8-45D9-A846-C5A2ECB346B0" class="- topic/object "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">Check buffer plate </p></desc><param name="testid" value="156018" class="- topic/param "/><param name="target" value="NIL" class="- topic/param "/><param name="axmodule" value="None" class="- topic/param "/></object> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-AA56EB35-EF7A-4140-ABAF-4AB5E5ECD418" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Component</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Buffer plate 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the buffer plate is level. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-92369981-F020-4E62-9707-58F93D054214" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p ">The buffer plate has to be kept open with a distance holder while encoders are measured. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The pinch is closed and the buffer reset in the initialization phase. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Then the frame buffer door should be opened, after which a distance holder can be inserted to keep the buffer plate opened. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This distance holder should be centered, around 10 to 20 mm thick, and not scratch the buffer plate. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The measurement will be performed and indicate the offset between the left and right encoder. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Afterwards, the distance holder should be removed, without scratching the buffer plate, and the frame buffer door should be closed. 
</p><fig id="GUID-E116D725-7FB1-4555-9F54-3DE081C52158" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7CBBE31B-65E4-4FD8-8C61-DEF6F2F9160A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7CBBE31B-65E4-4FD8-8C61-DEF6F2F9160A-low.png"/></fig></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-69D2CD54-5B44-4236-AE10-A76F8E51C6CC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
